<html>
  <head>
    <%= stylesheet "prez" %>
    <%= stylesheet "fishing" %>
  </head>

  <body>
    <% slide do %>
      <h3> littleBits Color Code </h3>
      <p class="blue">
        Blue: Power
      </p>
      <p class="pink">
        Pink: Input
      </p>
      <p class="green">
        Green: Output
      </p>
      <p class="orange">
        Orange: Wire
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="blue"> Power </h3>
      <%= image "power" %>
     <p>
        This power module lets you use a 9 volt battery to supply electricity to your littleBits.<br/>
        Snap in the battery and cable and flip the switch to turn it on.
      </p>

      <% notes do %>
        <p>
          Always start your circuit with a blue power module.
        </p>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="green"> Bright LED </h3>
      <%= image "bright-led" %>
      <p>
        The bright LED (or "Light-Emitting Diode") is a small module that puts out a big light.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Challenge:  Make a Falshlight! </h3>
      <%= image "flashlight" %>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="green"> Bargraph </h3>
      <%= image "bargraph" %>
      <p>
        The bargraph has five LEDs in different colors that light up to show you how much signal the module is receiving.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="green"> DC Motor </h3>
      <%= image "dc-motor" %>
      <p>
        The DC (or "Direct Current") motor rotates a shaft when you send it an ON signal.
        It even has a switch to set the direction of rotation!
        It also includes the motorMate-- an accessory that makes it easy to attach
        wheels, paper, cardboard, and lots of other materials to the motor.
        Simply slide it on the "D" shape on the shaft.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="green"> Servo </h3>
      <%= image "servo" %>
      <p>
        The servo Bit is a controllable motor that can swing back and forth!
        It has two modes: in “Turn” mode, the input from other littleBits determines the position of the arm –
        try using a dimmer to set the angle you want.
        In “Swing” mode, the servo will move back and forth on its own – the input controls how fast it goes.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="pink"> Button </h3>
      <%= image "button" %>
      <p>
        The button Bit push to turn your creation on, and release to turn it off.
      </p>
      <% notes do %>
        <p>
          The button module will make or break the signal path between two modules.
          When the button is pressed, the output of the module is directly connected to the signal line input.
          When not pressed the output of the module is weakly pulled low through a 1meg resistor.
        </p>
      <% end %>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="pink"> Dimmer </h3>
      <%= image "dimmer" %>
      <p>
        The dimmer Bit lets you control your creations with a simple knob.
        Turn it clockwise to send more signal to the following Bits.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Challenge:  Enhance your flashlight! </h3>
      <%= image "flashlight" %>
      <p>
        Add on/off switch for your flashlight.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="pink"> Pulse </h3>
      <%= image "pulse" %>
      <p>
        The pulse Bit is like an electronic heartbeat.
        It sends out a stream of short ON signals,
        and you can make the speed of the pulses faster or slower using the included screwdriver.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Challenge:  Convert flashlight to strobe light! </h3>
      <%= image "strobe-light" %>
      <p>
        Add pulse to flashlight and adjust speed.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="orange"> Wire </h3>
      <%= image "wire" %>
      <p>
        The wire Bit is just what it sounds like - it allows you to physically separate your Bits.
        Try it whenever you need to break up your chain of Bits.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3 class="orange"> Branch </h3>
      <%= image "branch" %>
      <p>
        The Branch Bit gives you more options for connecting your Bits:
        it lets you connect the output of a single Bit to as many as three others,
        oriented in different directions.
        Use it when you want to trigger light, sound and motion at the same time.
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Fishing Game </h3>
      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/lisU5ziIu3M" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Fishing Game - Materials </h3>
      <%= image "fishing-game-materials", width: "560", heigh: "315" %>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Fishing Pole </h3>
      <%= image "fishing-pole", width: "560", heigh: "315" %>
      <br/>
      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zrrw9h426vs?list=PLgH5gyvrQYS46MW_LLNmciYKOJ_a_R7Ia" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      <p>
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Fishing Pond </h3>
      <%= image "fishing-pond", width: "560", heigh: "315" %>
      <br/>
      <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WETcYl978Oc?list=PLgH5gyvrQYS46MW_LLNmciYKOJ_a_R7Ia" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
      <p>
      </p>
    <% end %>

    <% slide do %>
      <h3> Thanks </h3>
      <p>
        <strong>
          Thank @onsitedotcom on twitter!<br/><br/>

          <u>My Info</u><br/>
          Twitter: @joeddean<br/>
          Email: joe.dean@gmail.com<br/>
        </strong>
      </p>
    <% end %>
  </body>
</html>
